      "location": "Marriott, Grand Ballroom",
      "description": "In a moment marked by climate urgency, market pressure, and rapid change, some leaders continue to make climate action central to how they do business. In this C-suite panel, executives will reflect on why strong climate values have shaped their companies in the past, continue to guide decision-making today, and remain essential to their vision for the future. The conversation will explore what it means to lead with conviction amid uncertainty, including how leaders stay grounded in values while navigating complexity and risk. Panelists will share how centering stewardship of people and planet is integral to building resilient businesses, strengthening trust, and supporting long-term growth.",
