      "description": "Join us for an in-depth session with biomedical scientist Rhonda Patrick, PhD, as she explores the critical role of omega-3 fatty acids in supporting cardiovascular, cognitive, and whole-body health.* EPA and DHA are essential structural components of every cell in the body, yet more than 80% of Americans are not meeting recommended intake levels through diet alone.† Drawing on decades of research in nutrition, metabolism, and aging, Dr. Patrick will unpack the latest science on omega-3s, their impact on long-term health outcomes, and why optimizing omega-3 status is foundational to supporting health across the lifespan.* Attendees will gain a deeper understanding of the evidence behind omega-3 supplementation and practical insights for translating this science into everyday health decisions. Free OmegaQuant Omega-3 Index Test Kit provided to all attendees. * These statements have not been evaluated by the Food and Drug Administration. This product is not intended to diagnose, treat, cure or prevent any disease. † Murphy RA, et al. BMJ Open. 2021.",
