      "timeLabel": "3:00 PM - 4:00 PM",
      "location": "Marriott, Grand Ballroom F",
      "description": "Many brands launch their products using thin supply chains—using a specialty ingredient or processing and ingredient in a new way. In fact, it’s central to their differentiation. But you can’t scale without a secure supply chain. Many brands start that journey by searching for a farmer. That can work, but it also could be a disaster for you and the farmer. Scaling organic and regenerative acreage depends on working through processors, mills, aggregators, and cooperatives that coordinate planting, pricing, logistics, and risk. In this candid conversation, farmers, processors, and founders will unpack: Who should be your first call? Meet your organic trade associations Why starting with finding a processor dramatically increases your odds of success How processors help align volume, rotation planning, and risk-sharing What “consistent customer at a consistent price” really means to a farmer How shared-risk pricing models unlock acreage How \"Farmer First Organic Pricing” will grow organic acreage and secure your supply What brands misunderstand about payment timing and capital when working with farmers Should you become a supplier or processor yourself to strengthen the entire chain If your brand depends on organic, regenerative, or specialty crops, this session will give you a practical roadmap for building supply the right way — from the middle out.",
      "eventType": "Organic & Regenerative Systems",
      "bannerUrl": "https://static.swapcard.com/public/images/77c36edcb3c24aecbfd05d2718cbf6da.png"
