      "description": "In today’s digital-first world, a single viral moment can put an ingredient or product on the map, but not every trend has staying power. How can brands distinguish between short-lived buzz and long-term opportunity? In this session, Spate will team up with MaryRuth’s to explore the path from virality to vitality: how online curiosity and social chatter evolve into sustainable consumer demand. Spate will share digital insights from Google Search, TikTok, and Instagram that reveal how consumers discover and adopt wellness trends, while MaryRuth’s will bring the brand perspective — how they’ve navigated viral moments, innovated around digital signals, and built trust with consumers along the way. Together, the speakers will provide a data-meets-brand view of what it takes to transform digital culture into real business growth. Attendees will: Understand how viral trends emerge in search and social data from Google Search, TikTok, and Instagram. Learn strategies to evaluate whether a viral trend has long-term potential. Gain insights from MaryRuth’s on how brands can authentically engage with digital culture. Walk away with a framework for connecting digital buzz to innovation and sustained consumer demand.",
