      "endIso": "2026-03-06T20:00:00.000Z",
      "timeLabel": "11:00 AM - 12:00 PM",
      "location": "Marriott, Grand Ballroom F",
      "description": "In today’s rapidly evolving world, wellness has become the new measure of wealth. Consumers are redefining what it means to live well, succeed, and thrive—reshaping culture, priorities, and behaviors across every generation. At the same time, we are entering an era where marketing to the algorithm, not the individual, determines visibility, influence, and growth. This presentation explores the forces reshaping the landscape and what brands must do to remain relevant. We begin with a look at where consumers have been, where they are today, and where they’re going—highlighting the cultural shifts and emerging priorities driving the wellness-as-wealth mindset. Tech acceleration, economic pressure, and lifestyle re-evaluation have created new attributes and meanings around wellness that extend beyond physical health to emotional, financial, and digital wellbeing. Increasingly, this expanded definition of wellness is anchored in a new aspiration: longevity—the pursuit of living better, longer. Consumers are prioritizing not only health-span, but overall lifespan, viewing wellness as an integrated, long-term investment designed to extend vitality, resilience, and quality of life across the years. Amid this transformation, two major inflection points are occurring simultaneously: a generational power shift and the rise of the K-economy. Together, these shifts are influencing how consumers make decisions, how communities form, and how trust is built. We will explore how these forces drive behavior change, influencing everything from purchasing decisions to digital engagement patterns, helping companies and brands adapt by understanding new behavioral signals, new cultural drivers, and new pathways to influence.",
